# PART 3 — PORTFOLIO & PROJECT PAGES

Kamiyon Studio Website Specification v2.0

---

## OBJECTIVE

The portfolio sells confidence through curated work — not a generic Behance grid.

Every project page should answer: **"Can Kamiyon Studio deliver work like this for me?"**

**Layout reference:** Fully Illustrated portfolio pattern (category bands → category list → project detail), rendered in **Kamiyon light mode**.

---

## INFORMATION ARCHITECTURE

```
/portfolio                              → Category hub
/portfolio/[category]                   → Project list
/portfolio/[category]/[slug]            → Project detail
```

### Categories

| Slug | Label |
| --- | --- |
| `design` | Design |
| `illustration` | Illustration |
| `games` | Games |
| `branding` | Branding |
| `3d-motion` | 3D & Motion |
| `web` | Web |

---

## LEVEL 1 — PORTFOLIO HUB (`/portfolio`)

**Purpose:** Orient visitors and route them to a discipline.

**Hero**

- Page title: "Portfolio" (or "Work")
- Intro line: one sentence — e.g. "Select a category to explore our work."
- Optional: "Select a category" dropdown / jump menu anchoring to bands

**Category bands (6 stacked full-width sections)**

Each band contains:

| Element | Spec |
| --- | --- |
| Background | Category collage or representative imagery (full-bleed) |
| Overlay panel | Semi-transparent panel (ensure AA contrast) with title + description |
| Title | Category name (large Montserrat) |
| Description | 2–3 lines on what Kamiyon delivers in this discipline |
| CTA | "View the portfolio" → `/portfolio/[category]` |

**Light-mode treatment**

- White or dark overlay text panel on imagery — never low-contrast text on busy photos
- Pink CTA links/buttons
- Subtle hover: band scale 1.01 or overlay brighten — no heavy animation

**Band order (top to bottom)**

1. Design
2. Illustration
3. Games
4. Branding
5. 3D & Motion
6. Web

---

## LEVEL 2 — CATEGORY PAGE (`/portfolio/[category]`)

**Purpose:** Showcase all projects within one discipline.

**Header**

- Category title (e.g. "Games")
- Intro paragraph: 1–2 sentences
- Optional: "Select a project" quick-nav dropdown

**Featured / latest project**

- Large hero image (full content width)
- Metadata bar below hero:
  - Status label (e.g. "Featured") in pink
  - Project title (bold)
  - Platform / tag list (muted, caps optional)
  - Short description (1–2 sentences, right-aligned or below on mobile)

**Project grid**

- Responsive: 3 cols desktop, 2 tablet, 1 mobile
- Each card:
  - Thumbnail (16:9)
  - Title
  - Subtitle or type tag (pink accent text)
  - Optional year
- Entire card clickable → `/portfolio/[category]/[slug]`
- Hover: slight zoom + soft shadow + pink accent glow

**Empty state**

- Kami-chan illustration
- Message: "Projects coming soon."
- Link back to `/portfolio`

**Pagination**

- "Load more" button preferred over infinite scroll (SEO + navigation)

---

## LEVEL 3 — PROJECT DETAIL (`/portfolio/[category]/[slug]`)

**Purpose:** Present one project as a focused case presentation.

**Inspired by:** Wulverblade / Mini Legends reference layouts — hero + gallery + sidebar.

### Hero

- Full-width feature image (game art, design mockup, illustration, etc.)
- Optional: soft gradient fade from image into white content area below

### Main layout (desktop)

| Column | Width | Content |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Gallery | ~65% | Primary image + thumbnail grid (2–4 columns) |
| Sidebar | ~35% | Project metadata + description + CTAs |

**Mobile:** stack — hero → metadata → gallery

### Sidebar / metadata

| Field | Notes |
| --- | --- |
| Title | Large, Montserrat |
| Client | If applicable; link if public |
| Category | Label + link back to category page |
| Platforms | e.g. PC, Mobile, Web |
| Year | |
| Location | If relevant |
| Description | 2–4 short paragraphs max |

### CTAs

| Button | When |
| --- | --- |
| Discuss Similar Project | Always → `/contact` |
| View Live / External Link | If `externalUrl` exists |
| Download Press Assets | If applicable → `/pres` |

### Gallery

- Thumbnail grid below or beside primary image
- Click thumbnail to swap primary view (client-side, no page reload)
- Rounded corners 16–24px, soft shadow
- Alt text on every image

### What NOT to include in v1

- Fake download/revenue metrics
- Fabricated client testimonials
- Full long-form case study sections (Challenge / Solution / Process) unless content exists in canon
- "Buy now" platform buttons (unless product has real store links)

