## CONTENT MODEL (static v1)

```typescript
type PortfolioCategory = {
  slug: string
  label: string
  description: string
  bandImage: string
  heroImage?: string
}

type PortfolioProject = {
  slug: string
  category: string
  title: string
  subtitle?: string
  client?: string
  location?: string
  year?: number
  platforms?: string[]
  tags?: string[]
  description: string
  heroImage: string
  gallery: string[]
  featured?: boolean
  externalUrl?: string
}
```

Seed 1–2 placeholder projects per category; label placeholders visibly.

---

## PHOTOGRAPHY & MEDIA

- Screenshots and artwork dominate
- No fake device mockups
- Mix: final deliverables, process sketches, UI captures where available
- Lazy-load below-fold images; use next-gen formats (WebP/AVIF)

---

## SEO (per project page)

- Unique `<title>`: `{Project Name} | {Category} | Kamiyon Studio`
- Unique meta description (150–160 chars)
- Open Graph image: project hero
- Breadcrumb: Portfolio → {Category} → {Project}
- Semantic headings: one H1 per page
- Image alt text

---

## RESPONSIVE

| Viewport | Grid | Hero |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Desktop | 3 columns | Side-by-side gallery + sidebar |
| Tablet | 2 columns | Stacked or narrowed sidebar |
| Mobile | 1 column | Full-width hero, stacked content |

---

## ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA

- [ ] Hub → category → project navigation works end-to-end
- [ ] All 6 categories have hub bands and list routes
- [ ] Light mode throughout; AA contrast on overlays
- [ ] Placeholder projects labeled; no fabricated clients
- [ ] Gallery and external links functional
- [ ] Breadcrumbs and SEO metadata present

